-- Hamilton of McLaren Wins Hungarian Grand Prix; Raikkonen Second
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-07-29T13:53:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-29/hamilton-of-mclaren-wins-hungarian-grand-prix-raikkonen-second.html
Lewis Hamilton  of McLaren won
today’s Hungarian Grand Prix for his second win in this year’s
Formula One championship.  Lotus duo Kimi Raikkonen and  Romain Grosjean  were second
and third after 69 laps of the Hungaroring near Budapest.  It was Hamilton’s third victory in the race and the 19th of
his career. Fernando Alonso of Ferrari, fifth, extended his lead
in the drivers' standings  Formula One now takes a break before the Belgian Grand Prix,
the 12th in a 20-race series, at Spa-Francorchamps on Sept. 2.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  